    "description": "Nippon Felt Co., Ltd. manufactures and sells press felts, shoe press belts, and industrial textile products in Japan, Asia, and internationally. It offers papermaking felts and pulp-making felts; felt for slate and building materials manufacturing; synthetic textiles; filter cloths, heat-resistant felts, sanforized blankets, felt for pleat-making machines, felt for conveyor belts, felts for waste treatment, etc.; industrial tubular needle-felts for industrial use; industrial woven jackets; industrial detergents and chemicals; and high-pressure shower equipment for papermaking. The company also engages in producing, finishing, and selling felt for making paper, pulp, slate, and other industrial applications; and industrial machinery and anti-pollution devices, as well as leasing and managing of real estate. Nippon Felt Co., Ltd. was incorporated in 1917 and is headquartered in Kita, Japan."
